10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1551 of Title 6, unless there is
13 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Oklahoma Money
15 Transmission Modernization Act”.
16 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1552 of Title 6, unless there is
18 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 The Oklahoma Money Transmission Modernization Act replaces
20 existing state money transmission laws. It is the intent of the
21 Legislature that the provisions of this act accomplish the
22 following:
23
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 6

1 1. Ensure states can coordinate in all areas of regulation,
2 licensing, and supervision to eliminate unnecessary regulatory
3 burden and more effectively utilize regulator resources;
4 2. Protect the public from financial crime;
5 3. Standardize the types of activities that are subject to
6 licensing or otherwise exempt from licensing; and
7 4. Modernize safety and soundness requirements to ensure
8 customer funds are protected in an environment that supports
9 innovative and competitive business practices.
10 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1553 of Title 6, unless there is
12 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 As used in the Oklahoma Money Transmission Modernization Act:
14 1. “Acting in concert” means persons knowingly acting together
15 with a common goal of jointly acquiring control of a licensee
16 whether or not pursuant to an express agreement;
17 2. “Authorized delegate” means any person a licensee designates
18 to engage in money transmission on behalf of the licensee;
19 3. “Average daily money transmission liability” means the
20 amount of the licensee’s outstanding money transmission obligations
21 in Oklahoma at the end of each day in a given period of time, added
22 together, and divided by the total number of days in the given
23 period of time. For purposes of calculating average daily money
24 transmission liability under this act for any licensee required to
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 7

1 do s o, the given period of time shall be the quarters ending March
2 31, June 30, September 30, and December 31;
3 4. “Bank Secrecy Act” means the Bank Secrecy Act, 31 U.S.C.,
4 Section 5311 et seq. and its implementing regulations, as amended
5 and recodified from time to time;
6 5. “Closed loop stored value” means stored value that is
7 redeemable by the issuer only for goods or services provided by the
8 issuer or its affiliate or franchisees of the issuer or its
9 affiliate, except to the extent required by applicable law to be
10 redeemable in cash for its cash value;
11 6. “Commissioner” means the State Banking Commissioner of the
12 Oklahoma State Banking Department as provided for in subsection B of
13 Section 201 of Title 6 of the Oklahoma Statutes or a person
14 designated by the Commissioner and acting under the Commissioner’s
15 direction and authority;
16 7. a. “Control” means a controlling influence as determined
17 by the Commissioner, or the power to:
18 (1) directly or indirectly vote at least twenty-five
19 percent (25%) of the outstanding voting shares or
20 voting interests of a licensee or person in
21 control of a licensee,
22 (2) elect or appoint a majority of key individuals or
23 executive officers, managers, directors,
24 trustees, or other persons exercising managerial
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 8

1 authority over a person in control of a licensee,
2 or
3 (3) directly or indirectly exercise a controlling
4 influence over the management or policies of a
5 licensee or person in control of a licensee.
6 b. A person is presumed to exercise a controlling
7 influence when the person holds the power to vote,
8 directly or indirectly, at least ten percent (10%) of
9 the outstanding voting shares or voting interests of a
10 licensee or person in control of a licensee. The
11 presumption of control defined by this subparagraph
12 may be rebutted by evidence that the person who is
13 presumed to exercise a controlling influence is a
14 passive investor.
15 c. For purposes of determining the percentage of a person
16 controlled by any other person, the person’s interest
17 shall be aggregated with the interest of any other
18 immediate family member, including the person’s
19 spouse, parents, children, siblings, mothers- and
20 fathers-in-law, sons- and daughters-in-law, brothers-
21 and sisters-in-law, and any other person who shares
22 such person’s home.
23 d. The Commissioner shall have broad authority to
24 designate a person as someone who has controlling
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 9

1 influence if the person owns voting shares of a
2 licensee or if the person acts on behalf of someone
3 who owns voting shares of a licensee. A determination
4 made by the Commissioner under this paragraph is not
5 rebuttable;
6 8. “Currency” means the coin and paper money issued by the
7 United States or another country that is designated as legal tender,
8 circulates, and is customarily used and accepted as a medium of
9 exchange in the country of issuance;
10 9. “Department” means the Oklahoma State Banking Department;
11 10. “Digital asset” means the same as defined in Section 1520
12 of Title 6 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
13 11. “Digital asset kiosk” means the same as defined in Section
14 1520 of Title 6 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
15 12. “Digital asset kiosk operator” means the same as defined in
16 Section 1520 of Title 6 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
17 13. “Eligible rating” means a sufficiently high credit rating
18 given by an eligible rating service. If a security has differing
19 credit ratings given by multiple eligible rating services, the
20 highest rating shall apply when determining whether the security has
21 an eligible rating. For purposes of this definition, a sufficiently
22 high credit rating is a credit rating of any of the three highest
23 rating categories provided by an eligible rating service, including:
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 10

