15 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1554 of Title 6, unless there is
17 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 The Oklahoma Money Transmission Modernization Act shall not
19 apply to:
20 1. An operator of a payment system to the extent that it
21 provides processing, clearing, or settlement services, between or
22 among persons exempted by this section or licensees, in connection
23 with wire transfers, credit card transactions, debit card
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 18

1 tran sactions, stored-value transactions, automated clearing house
2 transfers, or similar funds transfers;
3 2. A person appointed as an agent of a payee to collect and
4 process a payment from a payor to the payee for goods or services,
5 other than money transmission itself, provided to the payor by the
6 payee, provided that:
7 a. there exists a written agreement between the payee
8 and the agent directing the agent to collect and
9 process payments from payors on the payee’s behalf,
10 b. the payee holds the agent out to the public as
11 accepting payments for goods or services on the
12 payee’s behalf, and
13 c. payment for the goods or services is treated as
14 received by the payee upon receipt by the agent so
15 that the payor’s obligation is extinguished and there
16 is no risk of loss to the payor if the agent fails to
17 remit the funds to the payee;
18 3. A person that acts as an intermediary by processing payments
19 between an entity that has directly incurred an outstanding money
20 transmission obligation to a sender, and the sender’s designated
21 recipient, provided that the entity:
22 a. is properly licensed or exempt from licensing
23 requirements under this act,
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 19

1 b. provides a receipt, electronic record, or other
2 written confirmation to the sender identifying the
3 entity as the provider of money transmission in the
4 transaction, and
5 c. bears sole responsibility to satisfy the outstanding
6 money transmission obligation to the sender,
7 including the obligation to make the sender whole in
8 connection with any failure to transmit the funds to
9 the sender’s designated recipient;
10 4. The United States or a department, agency, or
11 instrumentality thereof, or its agent;
12 5. Money transmission by the United States Postal Service or by
13 an agent of the United States Postal Service;
14 6. A state, county, city, or any other governmental agency or
15 governmental subdivision or instrumentality of a state, or its
16 agent;
17 7. A federally insured depository financial institution, bank
18 holding company, office of an international banking corporation,
19 foreign bank that establishes a federal branch pursuant to the
20 International Banking Act of 1978, 12 U.S.C., Section 3101 et seq.,
21 as amended, corporation organized pursuant to the Bank Service
22 Company Act, 12 U.S.C., Sections 1861 through 1867, as amended, or
23 corporation organized under the Edge Act, 12 U.S.C., Sections 611
24 through 633, as amended;
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 20

1 8. Electronic funds transfer of governmental benefits for a
2 federal, state, county, or governmental agency by a contractor on
3 behalf of the United States or a department, agency, or
4 instrumentality thereof, or on behalf of a state or governmental
5 subdivision, agency, or instrumentality thereof;
6 9. A board of trade designated as a contract market under the
7 Commodity Exchange Act, 7 U.S.C., Sections 1 through 25, as amended,
8 or a person that, in the ordinary course of business, provides
9 clearance and settlement services for a board of trade to the extent
10 of its operation as or for such a board;
11 10. A registered futures commission merchant under the federal
12 commodities laws to the extent of its operation as such a merchant;
13 11. A person registered as a securities broker-dealer under
14 federal or state securities laws to the extent of its operation as
15 such a broker-dealer;
16 12. An individual employed by a licensee, authorized delegate,
17 or any person exempted from the licensing requirements of this act
18 when acting within the scope of employment and under the supervision
19 of the licensee, authorized delegate, or exempted person as an
20 employee and not as an independent contractor;
21 13. A person expressly appointed as a third-party service
22 provider to or agent of an entity exempt under paragraph 7 of this
23 section, solely to the extent that:
24
