24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 22

1 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1556 of Title 6, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. In order to carry out the purposes of the Oklahoma Money
5 Transmission Modernization Act, the Commissioner may, subject to the
6 provisions of subsections A and B of Section 7 of this act:
7 1. Enter into agreements or relationships with other government
8 officials or federal and state regulatory agencies and regulatory
9 associations to improve efficiencies and reduce regulatory burden by
10 standardizing methods or procedures and sharing resources, records,
11 or related information obtained under this act;
12 2. Use, hire, contract, or employ analytical systems, methods,
13 or software to examine or investigate any person subject to this
14 act;
15 3. Accept from other state or federal government agencies or
16 officials licensing, examination, or investigation reports created
17 by such other state or federal government agencies or officials; and
18 4. Accept audit reports made by an independent certified public
19 accountant or other qualified third-party auditor for an applicant
20 or licensee and incorporate the audit report into any report of
21 examination or investigation.
22 B. The Commissioner shall have broad administrative authority
23 to:
24 1. Administer, interpret, and enforce this act;
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 23

1 2. Promulgate rules implementing this act; and
2 3. Recover the cost of administering and enforcing this act by
3 imposing and collecting proportionate and equitable fees and costs
4 associated with applications, examinations, investigations, and
5 other actions required for the purposes of this act.
6 SECTION 7. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1557 of Title 6, unless there is
8 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 A. Except as otherwise provided in subsection B of this
10 section, all information or reports obtained by the Commissioner
11 from an applicant, licensee, or authorized delegate, and all
12 information contained in or related to an examination,
13 investigation, operating report, or condition report prepared by, on
14 behalf of, or for the use of the Commissioner, or financial
15 statements, balance sheets, or authorized delegate information, are
16 confidential and are not subject to disclosure under the Oklahoma
17 Open Records Act.
18 B. The Commissioner may disclose information not otherwise
19 subject to disclosure under subsection A of this section to
20 representatives of state or federal agencies who agree in a record
21 that they will maintain the confidentiality of the information or
22 where the Commissioner finds that the release is reasonably
23 necessary for the protection and interest of the public in
24 accordance with the Oklahoma Open Records Act.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 24

1 C. This section shall not prohibit the Commissioner from
2 disclosing to the public a list of all licensees or the aggregated
3 financial or transactional data concerning those licensees.
