22 SECTION 8. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1558 of Title 6, unless there is
24 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 25

1 A. The Commissioner may conduct investigations in or outside
2 this state and the United States as the Commissioner considers
3 necessary or appropriate to administer and enforce the Oklahoma
4 Money Transmission Modernization Act.
5 B. For purposes of an investigation, examination, or other
6 proceeding under this act, the Commissioner may:
7 1. Administer oaths or cause oaths to be administered;
8 2. Subpoena witnesses;
9 3. Compel the attendance of witnesses;
10 4. Take evidence; and
11 5. Require the production of any document that the Commissioner
12 determines to be relevant to the inquiry.
13 C. If a person refuses to obey a subpoena, the District Court
14 of Oklahoma County, on application by the Commissioner, may issue an
15 order requiring the person to appear before the Commissioner and
16 produce documents or give evidence regarding the matter under
17 investigation.
18 D. The Commissioner may employ a person, request the Attorney
19 General, or request any other state, federal, or local law
20 enforcement agency to assist in enforcing this act.
21 E. The Commissioner may recover the reasonable costs incurred
22 in connection with an investigation conducted under this act from
23 the person that is the subject of the investigation.
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 26

1 SECTION 9. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1559 of Title 6, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The Commissioner may conduct an examination or investigation
5 of a licensee or authorized delegate or otherwise take independent
6 action authorized by this act or by a rule adopted or order issued
7 under this act as reasonably necessary or appropriate to administer
8 and enforce this act, regulations promulgated pursuant to this act,
9 and other applicable law, including the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA
10 PATRIOT Act. The Commissioner may:
11 1. Conduct an examination either on-site or off-site;
12 2. Conduct an examination in conjunction with an examination
