8 SECTION 16. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1566 of Title 6, unless there is
10 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 A. When an application for an original license under this act
12 is determined by the Commissioner to include all the items and
13 address all the matters that are required, the application shall be
14 deemed complete and the Commissioner shall notify the applicant in
15 writing of the date on which the application was deemed complete,
16 and:
17 1. The Commissioner shall approve or deny the application
18 within one hundred eighty (180) days after the completion date; or
19 2. The Commissioner may extend the review period at the
20 Commissioner’s discretion.
21 B. A determination by the Commissioner that an application is
22 complete and is accepted for processing shall mean only that the
23 application, on its face, appears to include all of the items,
24 including the criminal background check response, and address all of
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 39

1 the matters that are required. A determination by the Commissioner
2 that an application is complete and accepted for processing shall
3 not be considered a determination of the application or of the
4 sufficiency of the information provided.
5 C. When an application is filed and considered complete, the
6 Commissioner shall investigate the applicant’s financial condition
7 and responsibility, financial and business experience, character,
8 and general fitness. The Commissioner may conduct an on-site
9 investigation of the applicant. The applicant shall pay the
10 reasonable cost of any on-site investigation. The Commissioner may
11 issue a license to an applicant under this section if the
12 Commissioner finds all the following conditions have been fulfilled:
13 1. The applicant has complied with Sections 14 and 15 of this
14 act; and
15 2. The financial condition and responsibility, financial and
16 business experience, competence, character, and general fitness of
17 the applicant, and the competence, experience, character, and
18 general fitness of the key individuals and persons in control of the
19 applicant, indicate that it is in the best interest of the public to
20 permit the applicant to engage in money transmission.
21 D. If an applicant avails itself or is otherwise subject to a
22 multistate licensing process:
23 1. The Commissioner shall be authorized and encouraged to
24 accept the investigation results of a lead investigative state for
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 40

1 the purpose of subsection C of this section if the lead
2 investigative state has sufficient staffing, expertise, and meets
3 the minimum standards; or
4 2. If Oklahoma is a lead investigative state, the Commissioner
5 shall be authorized and encouraged to investigate the applicant
6 pursuant to subsection C of this section and the timeframes
7 established by agreement through the multistate licensing process;
8 provided, however, in no case shall such timeframe be noncompliant
9 with the application period provided in paragraph 1 of subsection A
10 of this section.
11 E. The Commissioner shall issue a formal written notice of the
12 denial of a license application within thirty (30) days of the
13 decision to deny the application. The Commissioner shall set forth
14 in the notice of denial the specific reasons for the denial of the
15 application. If an applicant whose application is denied by the
16 Commissioner under this section chooses to appeal the denial, the
17 applicant shall file an appeal with the Oklahoma State Banking Board
18 within fifteen (15) calendar days after the date of the written
19 notice of the denial.
20 F. The Commissioner may deny a license application if the
21 applicant has not received approval to operate as a money
22 transmitter in the state in which it is organized and the state in
23 which its main office is located. The Commissioner may deny a
24 license application based on the findings of another state.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 41

