13 Transmission Modernization Act.
14 1. Any digital asset kiosk operator acting in violation of this
15 subsection shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor,
16 punishable by a fine not less than Six Hundred Dollars ($600.00) nor
17 more than Two Thousand Dollars ($2,000.00) per violation, or by
18 imprisonment in the county jail for not less than thirty (30) days
19 nor more than one (1) year, or by both such fine and imprisonment.
20 2. Any digital asset kiosk which is used operated by a digital
21 asset kiosk operator in violation of this subsection may be seized
22 at the direction of the Attorney General by any commissioned peace
23 officer in this state. The procedures set forth in Section 1738 of
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3521 Page 84

1 Titl e 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes shall apply to any digital asset
2 kiosk seized under this subsection.
